Covariant return type allows overriding method to return subclass of original return type.

```java
class Animal {
    Animal getAnimal() {
        return new Animal();
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    @Override
    Dog getAnimal() {  // Returns Dog instead of Animal (subclass)
        return new Dog();
    }
}

class Labrador extends Dog {
    @Override
    Labrador getAnimal() {  // Further narrowed return type
        return new Labrador();
    }
}

// Usage
Animal a = new Dog();
Dog d = a.getAnimal();  // Valid because covariant return type
